<div id="review_1367424726" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1367424726" />
    <a title="Brian Switek" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/398102-brian-switek"><img alt="Brian Switek" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1441921405p2/398102.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1367424726?book_show_action=true">Aug 18, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Brian Switek" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Brian Switek" href="/user/show/398102-brian-switek">Brian Switek</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780374516901" href="/book/show/19894.Basin_and_Range">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1367424726" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5537578991952121665">I feel a little bad giving this book less than five stars. It&apos;s supposed to be an all-time classic for the geologically-minded. But while McPhee weaves some lovely geopoetry on his journey, intrusions in his prose can be denser than the rocks he&apos;s trying to describe. He&apos;s at his best when rhapsodizing about ideas and history, which the great expanses of the west certainly bring to mind.</span>
  <span id="freeText5537578991952121665" style="display:none">I feel a little bad giving this book less than five stars. It's supposed to be an all-time classic for the geologically-minded. But while McPhee weaves some lovely geopoetry on his journey, intrusions in his prose can be denser than the rocks he's trying to describe. He's at his best when rhapsodizing about ideas and history, which the great expanses of the west certainly bring to mind.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5537578991952121665" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


